  "text": "where w T (x;~ ) is the temperance utility premium de…ned by [CITATION_1] . Here w(x; Y; X) is the 4th-order utility premium. It measures the degree of pain due to the passage from Y to X with X 4 Y . (11) by showing that mixed risk aversion ensures mutual aggravation of risk changes i.e. the decision maker's trait of perceiving two risk changes as mutually aggravating. They rewrote Eq. (11) equivalently as:",
